title: Software Engineer I (Full Time) United States

Description: pstrongWho The Flip Is Flip?strongpbrpEver have a bad experience calling customer service? We're changing that!pbrpFlip replaces old customer service phone robots with a modern "Alexa"-like voice AI experience for 200+ of the best companies on the planet in eCommerce and Transportation (more verticals coming soon!). We talk to millions of people weekly and have helped 200M+ callers so far.pbrpIn 5 years the idea of bad customer service will be a relic of the past, thanks to products like Flip. 1% of companies have adopted this technology today and yet everyone agrees it is obvious, inevitable, and imminent ‚Äì we aim to lead this charge and win this market.pbrpFlip is a profitable, fast-growing and well-funded 30-person startup based in NYC, LA, and the UK. Our team is the most important and best thing we‚Äôve built.pbrpstrongWhat You‚Äôll DostrongpbrpWe are looking for a few great product engineers (backend software engineers that love building products) to join us in creating the next generation of our over-the-phone voice assistant.pAt Flip, you'll create user experiences, features, and oversee whole segments of the Flip assistant. You'll also get into the data, listen to our customers, and help shape the direction of the product. We have a few excellent senior engineers already on the team, one of which will become your direct mentor!pbrpstrongWho You Are, As An EngineerstrongulliGood on the backend, with (at least a bit of) Python experience - we're almost all backend here, because voice products have no GUI!liliYour engineering level: mid-level up to senior engineerliliThe product is what we're working on - not theoretical engineering perfection! :)liliYou care about the customerliulpbrpstrongWho You Are, As A PersonstrongulliLooking to go all-in, learn a lot, and do the best work of your career (so far!)liliPut in the time, and put out work you're proud ofliliCommunicate well, and embrace ownership, speed, &amp; occasional uncertaintyliliEager and willing to support your teammates - just like they will with you!liulpbrpstrongBonusesstrongulliKnow what it looks like to work at a startup, and have an entrepreneurial driveliliExperience building Voice products - but we can teach you this too :)liliOffices in Dumbo, NY and Playa Vista, CA - work onsite in either location!liulpbrpstrongMore About UsstrongulliWe're international, spanning the US, UK, and CanadaliliOur tech stack includes Python, MongoDB, AWS, Twilio, Datadog, Snowflake, and LookerliliWe are backed by ScOp Venture Capital, Bullpen Capital, and Forum Ventures, as well as founders &amp; executives from Amazon Alexa, Ada, Attentive, and SimonliliComprehensive healthcare and unlimited vacation, including a mandatory half week for everyone over July 4, and a full week off at the end of the yearliulpbrpOur customers span the globe, and so do our offices. Flip is committed to providing equal employment opportunities for all employees, applicants, and covered individuals regardless of protected characteristics. We want our company to be as diverse and inclusive as our customers.

title: Software Engineer

Description: At Lyft, our mission is to improve people‚Äôs lives with the world‚Äôs best transportation. To do this, we start with our own community by creating an open, inclusive, and diverse organization.brbrWe care deeply about delivering the best transportation experience; this means the best experience for the passenger and the best experience for the driver. We believe this quality of service can only be achieved with a deep understanding of our world, our cities, our streets‚Ä¶ how they evolve, how they breathe.brbrInterns work side-by-side with top engineers in the industry while having autonomy from the get-go. They contribute to user-facing products and are able to see their work go live quickly. Lyft fosters a collaborative environment in the office, so there's always a sharp mind eager to hear about your next idea. So what's yours?brbrstrongResponsibilities:brbrstrongulliOwn your project, while checking in with other team members throughout the day with questions and updatesliliYou leave the code in a better state than when you found it (progressive refactor)liliYou value reliability, ensured by testing (unit, integration and load tests)liliParticipate in code reviews to ensure code quality and distribute knowledgeliliContinuous integration and deploymentliliGo home knowing that your work today is meaningfully improving the lives of every Lyft driver and every Lyft passenger!brbrliulstrongExperience:brbrstrongulliCurrently pursuing a Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, with a graduation date between December 2025 and Summer 2026 (required)liliAvailable during Summer 2025 for an internship in San FranciscoliliKnowledge of JavaScript, CSS, and HTMLliliExperience working with leading JavaScript frameworks, like ReactliliUnderstanding of how browsers and DOM workliliExperience with Git or other distributed version control systemsliliExperience with browser developer toolsliliExperience with the Unix command line interfaceliliSolid understanding of web performanceliliExperience with TypeScriptliliExperience with CSS preprocessors like SassliliUnderstanding of unit, integration, and end-to-end testingliliExperience with modern frontend testing tools, such as Webpack, Babel, Jest, Jasmine, Protractor, and WebDriverliliExcellent communication skillsliliPassion for community, sustainability, andor transportationliliAbility to thrive in a startup environmentliliExperience solving real-time technology problemsliliPrevious work with social networksbrbrliulstrongBenefits:brbrstrongulliGreat medical, dental, and vision insurance optionsliliMental health benefitsliliIn addition to holidays, interns receive 2 days paid time off and 3 days sick time offlili401(k) plan to help save for your futureliliPre-tax commuter benefitsliliLyft Pink - Lyft team members get an exclusive opportunity to test new benefits of our Ridership ProgrambrbrliulemBenefits are available for Lyft team members who work 30 or more hours per week. Please request information about benefits available to team members who work 29 hours or less per week.brbrememLyft is an equal opportunityaffirmative action employer committed to an inclusive and diverse workplace. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regards to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status or any other basis prohibited by law. We also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories consistent with applicable federal, state and local law.brbrememThis role will be in-office on a hybrid schedule ‚Äî Team Members will be expected to work in the office 3 days per week on Mondays, Thursdays and a team-specific third day. brbrememThe expected range of pay for this position in the San Francisco Bay Area is $52.00 - $58.00hour. Salary ranges are dependent on a variety of factors, including qualifications, experience and geographic location. Your recruiter can share more information about the salary range specific to your working location and other factors during the hiring process.em
title: Software Developer -- Entry Level

Description: Applications are accepted until further notice.brbrPlease note this posting is to advertise potential job opportunities. This exact role may not be open today but could open in the near future. When you apply, a Cisco representative may contact you directly if a relevant position opens.brbrWho You‚Äôll Work WithbrbrOur hardworking team members are busy programming magic across the globe on teams such as Engineering, Information Technology, Supply Chain, Customer Experience, Security and Trust, etc.brbrYou would play a crucial role in driving next-gen software innovations including cloud, mobile, desktop or security spaces. On any of these teams, you'll get hands-on experience working with applications that make technology accessible no matter what device they‚Äôre on. See the possibilities when creativity meets design and build solutions which will transform how we work, live, learn, and play.brbrWhat You‚Äôll DobrbrOur software engineers are the gurus behind the scenes ensuring all of our programs are easy to use and bug free. Using a keen eye, you‚Äôll develop software and tools in support of many of our high-impact technology platforms such as operating systems, networks, databases and more. While we‚Äôre growing in the software business, you‚Äôll still need to see the big picture and watch for hardware compatibility while even potentially influencing design.brbrWho You ArebrbrA software developer who demonstrates exceptional communication and collaboration abilities, coupled with a genuine enthusiasm for tackling complex challenges. The ideal candidate will exhibit outstanding organizational skills and a keen aptitude for managing their time efficiently.brbrAs a process-driven individual, you will have a fervent desire to streamline and enhance existing procedures. Your adeptness in time management will empower you to effectively prioritize tasks and deliver high-quality work within set deadlines.brbrJoin our team and apply your passion for problem-solving to create innovative software solutions that make a difference.brbrstrongMinimum Qualificationsbrbrstrongulli Including but not limited to a graduateupcoming graduate of a technical degree or certification program from a Technical Boot Camp, Apprenticeship, Community College or 4-year University. lili Open to 0-3 years of relevant experience or recent graduate or those in the final year of a Bachelor's in Computer Science , Software Engineering, Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering, a related program, or holders of equivalent academic certifications. lili Up-to-date on programming and scripting languages: CC++, Python, andor Java lili Hands on QA, Testing, andor Debugging skills lili Able to legally live and work in the country for which you‚Äôre applying, without visa support or sponsorship brbrliulstrongPreferred Qualificationsbrbrstrongulli Knowledge of Linux, Networking concepts, OS fundamentals, Embedded Development, andor ML lili Experience with Databases, Web Application Development, and Web Services lili Knowledge in Computer Networking andor Cybersecurity lili Knowledge of Cloud Platforms: AWS, Microsoft Azure, or Google Cloud brbrliulstrongWhy Ciscobrbrstrong#WeAreCisco, where each person is unique, but we bring our talents to work as a team and make a difference powering an inclusive future for all.brbrWe embrace digital, and help our customers implement change in their digital businesses. Some may think we‚Äôre ‚Äúold‚Äù (40 years strong) and only about hardware, but we‚Äôre also a software company. And a security company. We even invented an intuitive network that adapts, predicts, learns and protects. No other company can do what we do ‚Äì you can‚Äôt put us in a box!brbrBut ‚ÄúDigital Transformation‚Äù is an empty buzz phrase without a culture that allows for innovation, creativity, and yes, even failure (if you learn from it.)brbrDay to day, we focus on the give and take. We give our best, give our egos a break, and give of ourselves (because giving back is built into our DNA.) We take accountability, bold steps, and take difference to heart. Because without diversity of thought and a dedication to equality for all, there is no moving forward.brbrSo, you have colorful hair? Don‚Äôt care. Tattoos? Show off your ink. Like polka dots? That‚Äôs cool. Pop culture geek? Many of us are. Passion for technology and world changing? Be you, with us!

Description: Applications are accepted until further notice.brbrPlease note this posting is to advertise potential job opportunities. This exact role may not be open today but could open in the near future. When you apply, a Cisco representative may contact you directly if a relevant position opens.brbrWho You‚Äôll Work WithbrbrOur hardworking team members are busy programming magic across the globe on teams such as Engineering, Information Technology, Supply Chain, Customer Experience, Security and Trust, etc.brbrYou would play a crucial role in driving next-gen software innovations including cloud, mobile, desktop or security spaces. While we‚Äôre growing in the software business, you‚Äôll still need to see the big picture and watch for hardware compatibility while even potentially influencing design.brbrUnsure where to start? Apply and explore all of the possibilities in: Applications Development, Database Development, Embedded Networking and OS Development, IT, Security, Test &amp; Quality, Web Services, etc.brbrWho You ArebrbrA software developer who demonstrates exceptional communication and collaboration abilities, coupled with a genuine enthusiasm for tackling complex challenges. The ideal candidate will exhibit outstanding organizational skills and a keen aptitude for managing their time efficiently.brbrAs a process-driven individual, you will have a fervent desire to streamline and enhance existing procedures. Your adeptness in time management will empower you to effectively prioritize tasks and deliver high-quality work within set deadlines.brbrJoin our team and apply your passion for problem-solving to create innovative software solutions that make a difference.brbrstrongMinimum Qualificationsbrbrstrongulli Currently enrolled in a full-time undergraduate program in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering or related field lili Up-to-date on programming and scripting languages: CC++, Python, andor Java lili Hands on QA, Testing, andor Debugging skills lili Able to legally live and work in the country for which you‚Äôre applying, without visa support or sponsorship brbrliulstrongPreferred Qualificationsbrbrstrongulli Knowledge of Linux, Networking concepts, OS fundamentals, Embedded Development, andor ML lili Experience with Databases, Web Application Development, and Web Services lili Knowledge in Computer Networking andor Cybersecurity lili Knowledge of Cloud Platforms: AWS, Microsoft Azure, or Google Cloud brbrliulstrongWhy Ciscobrbrstrong#WeAreCisco, where each person is unique, but we bring our talents to work as a team and make a difference powering an inclusive future for all.brbrWe embrace digital, and help our customers implement change in their digital businesses. Some may think we‚Äôre ‚Äúold‚Äù (40 years strong) and only about hardware, but we‚Äôre also a software company. And a security company. We even invented an intuitive network that adapts, predicts, learns and protects. No other company can do what we do ‚Äì you can‚Äôt put us in a box!brbrBut ‚ÄúDigital Transformation‚Äù is an empty buzz phrase without a culture that allows for innovation, creativity, and yes, even failure (if you learn from it.)brbrDay to day, we focus on the give and take. We give our best, give our egos a break, and give of ourselves (because giving back is built into our DNA.) We take accountability, bold steps, and take difference to heart. Because without diversity of thought and a dedication to equality for all, there is no moving forward.brbrSo, you have colorful hair? Don‚Äôt care. Tattoos? Show off your ink. Like polka dots? That‚Äôs cool. Pop culture geek? Many of us are. Passion for technology and world changing? Be you, with us!

Description: # 162668 - Piscataway, New Jersey, United StatesbrbrstrongWho We ArebrbrstrongColgate-Palmolive Company is a caring, innovative growth company that is reimagining a healthier future for all people, their pets and our planet. Focused on Oral Care, Personal Care, Home Care and Pet Nutrition, we sell our products in more than 200 countries and territories under brands such as Colgate, Palmolive, elmex, hello, meridol, Sorriso, Tom‚Äôs of Maine, EltaMD, Filorga, Irish Spring, PCA SKIN, Protex, Sanex, Softsoap, Speed Stick, Ajax, Axion, Fabuloso, Soupline and Suavitel, as well as Hill‚Äôs Pet Nutrition.brbrWe are recognized for our leadership and innovation in promoting sustainability and community wellbeing, including our achievements in decreasing plastic waste and promoting recyclability, saving water, conserving natural resources and improving children‚Äôs oral health.brbrIf you want to work for a company that lives by their values, then give your career a reason to smile and join our global team!brbrstrongAt Colgate-Palmolive, we offer an exceptional Internship Program within our Global Information Technology organization. This internship is a six-month paid hybrid program, starting in January and continuing into the spring semester as part-time with opportunity to extend. As an integral part of our team, interns will gain exposure to enterprise business practices and modern technologies. Each intern will contribute to new and existing projects through hands-on experience with software engineering, application configurations, and process implementation throughout the development lifecycle.brbrstrongstrongThe internship begins with a 2-week training session, designed to introduce interns to the company's culture, policies, and technologies. Afterwards, each intern is assigned to a unique project and dedicated mentor depending on the available projects and intern‚Äôs interests. Projects may involve Backend Development, Frontend Development, and more. brbrstrongstrongResponsibilities:brbrstrongulliEngage in mandatory 2-week training sessionliliParticipate on a team to design, configure, and build softwareliliMeet with direct team, stakeholders, and end-usersliliResearch to solve complex problemsliliDeliver presentation of results and contributions to leadershipliliAdditional responsibilities will be dependent upon specific project assignmentbrbrliulstrongRequirements:brbrstrongulliMust currently be enrolled in a Bachelor‚Äôs or Master‚Äôs degree program at a college or university with a graduation date of or later than May 2025liliMajoring in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Information Technology, or a related fieldliliDocumentation of authorization to work in the United States, not requiring visa sponsorship now or in the futureliliA minimum GPA of 2.8liliDemonstrated familiarity with programming languages through course or personal projectsliliPrevious work experience with software development or web-related technologies is a plus liliMust be available to work hybrid at our Piscataway, NJ office location throughout the entire internshipliulliEvery Tuesday or Wednesday, specific hours are flexible liulliThis position requires a 6-month commitment (January-June)liulliMust be available to work 35 hoursweek during the winter break and 15 hoursweek during the academic semesterbrliululstrongCompensation And BenefitsbrbrstrongSalary Range $23.00 - $32.50 USDbrbrPay is based on multiple non-discriminatory, individualized factors including but not limited to experience, job-related knowledge and education, skills and officemarket location. In addition to base salary, salaried employees are eligible for annual discretionary bonuses, profit-sharing and, for Executive-level (salary grade 16 and above) roles only, long-term incentives in the form of Restricted Stock Units andor Stock Options.brbrSubject to the terms and conditions of the applicable benefits plans then in effect, all salaried employees are also eligible for a competitive benefits package which includes:brbrulliInsurance: Employees (and their eligible dependents) are eligible to participate in Company-sponsored Medical, Dental, Vision, Basic Life Insurance, Accidental Death &amp; Dismemberment and Disability insurance plans. liliRetirement Plans: Employees are eligible to enroll in Colgate's 401(k) plan, which provides for company matching contributions subject to eligibility requirementsliliVacationPTO: Employees receive a minimum of 15 days of vacationPTO leave annuallyliliPaid Holidays: Employees receive a minimum of 13 paidfloating holidays annuallyliliPaid Sick Leave: Based on location and consistent with applicable state and local law, employees receive a minimum of 40 hours of paid sick leave on January 1st of each yearliliPaid Parental Leave: Eligible employees may take up to eight weeks of paid parental leave and 12 weeks of unpaid leave (varies for employees with fewer than 12 months of service and is subject to hours worked requirements)brbrliulstrongOur Commitment to SustainabilitybrbrstrongWith the Colgate brand in more homes than any other, we are presented with great opportunities and new challenges as we work to integrate sustainability into all aspects of our business and create positive social impact. We are determined to position ourselves for further growth as we act on our 2025 Sustainability &amp; Social Impact Strategy.brbrstrongOur Commitment to Diversity, Equity &amp; InclusionbrbrstrongAchieving our purpose starts with our people ‚Äî ensuring our workforce represents the people and communities we serve ‚Äîand creating an environment where our people feel they belong; where we can be our authentic selves, feel treated with respect and have the support of leadership to impact the business in a meaningful way.brbrstrongEqual Opportunity EmployerbrbrstrongColgate is an equal opportunity employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, national origin, ethnicity, age, disability, marital status, veteran status (United States positions), or any other characteristic protected by law.brbrReasonable accommodation during the application process is available for persons with disabilities. Please contact Application_Accommodation@colpal.com with the subject "Accommodation Request" should you require accommodation.brbrFor additional Colgate terms and conditions, please click here.brbr

Description: If you are interested in more than one Supernova role, please apply to your first preference. We will still consider you for all opportunities.brbrstrongWho We ArebrbrstrongOKX is revolutionising world systems through our cutting-edge digital asset exchange, Web3 portal and blockchain ecosystems. We are deeply committed to shaping a fairer, more transparent and accessible society through blockchain technology and to date, we have 50+ million users, 3000+ employees and 180+ countries believing in the same vision as us. We are safe and reliable, backed by our Proof of Reserves. As strong supporters of the Arts and Sports, we are proud partners of @McLarenF1 @ManCity @Tribeca.brbrstrongHiring TeamsbrbrstrongulliBackend: Our mission is to provide the best crypto trading experience in the world for our customers. We are focused on building a platform that can handle all complexities of money movement. This includes supporting different currencies, new payment methods, and integrating with banks globally to help our customers buy and sell their crypto assets seamlessly and flawlessly. liliMachine Learning: We apply state of the art AIML technology to resolve fraudscamtrust issues, conduct research and development, and build machine learning models to detect and control complex fraud attacks.liliCloud Infrastructure: Develop infrastructure to enhance and maintain systems that ensure high availability, scalability, and security for our platforms, supporting a seamless experience for users worldwide.liliBlockchain: Development and maintenance of our innovative platform, catering to a diverse range of users engaged in either Defi trading, smart contracts, blockchain analysis, NFT, secure wallet solutions, explorer, earn, onchain AML etc.brbrbrliulstrongAbout OKX Graduate Program (Supernova)brbrstrongThe Supernova Program is a 3-year Career Accelerator Program that aims to fast-track, high performing graduates into technical experts and future leaders mainly in the fields of Product Engineering, Product Management, and Product Design. We firmly believe in the power of the new era. Join us to achieve your narrative around crypto.brbrAs a graduate strongSoftware Engineerstrong, you will build and maintain the OKX platform with millions of daily active users. You will work cross-functionally with design, product, and other engineering teams to identify customer needs, and ship high-quality new features through fast iterations. This is an opportunity to learn the full life cycle of crypto platforms including proretail trading, asset management, and wallet.brbrstrongWhat You‚Äôll Be DoingbrbrstrongulliBe part of the global engineering team to design and develop cutting-edge crypto-linked products on the platform. Deliver customized solutions with performance, scalability and continuous integration in mind while maintaining overall architecture consistency. liliBe a problem solver to build high availability, high performance distributed service. Strive for optimization and maximize user satisfaction in a time-critical manner. liliPartner closely with Design, Product and Marketing teams, drive rapid innovation by turning design ideas into quality features that scale to millions of users. Communicate effectively to peers, cross-functions and leadership on project deliverables. liliStay on top of industry trends, and evaluate new solutions to address our unique and fast-growing business needs. Prototype ideas quickly using cutting edge technologies. liliMaintain high-quality technical documentation. Uphold technology best practices and code reviews with peers. Improve efficiency in cross-officetime zone collaboration. brbrbrliulstrongWhat We Look For In YoubrbrstrongulliBachelors in Computer Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics, related technical disciplines, or self-taught enthusiasts liliPossess relevant tech stack skillset for the respective specialisation - JavaSpringBootSpringCloud, Python, MicroserviceAPI development, JavaScript, ReactAngularVue, HTML5CSS3, KotlinObjective-CSwift, relational databases, data structures and algorithms. liliPassionate about the latest technology. Curious to learn all aspects of trading products in financial and crypto markets, including spot, future, swap, options, and structured products. liliAnalytical with positive problem-solving mindset, A pro-active team player that embodies a growth mindset, flexible and comfortable in navigating ambiguity with a global mindset liliExperience in practicing automated testing and continuous integration brbrbrliulstrongNice to HavesbrbrstrongulliExperience in internship freelance projects, designed and developed micro-service programs, or capability for cross-browser development.liliComfortable with the cloud-based Linux environment. Who we arebrbrstrongAbout StripebrbrstrongStripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies‚Äîfrom the world‚Äôs largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups‚Äîuse Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone‚Äôs reach while doing the most important work of your career.brbrstrongAbout The TeambrbrstrongOur internship program will provide an opportunity to work on meaningful products that will grow the GDP of the internet. Through the internship, you will work with many systems and technologies, gain experience in systems design and testing, and have opportunities to present your work to your team and the wider org. Each intern has a dedicated intern manager, and every project is part of the team‚Äôs roadmap and will directly help Stripe‚Äôs mission.brbrWhat you‚Äôll dobrbrEvery internship at Stripe centers around a real, legitimate project that our customers urgently need, touching many parts of our operations and stack. We will support you in shipping it. Yes, you will actually ship it. Some recent projects include rebuilding our statistics aggregation service, building new service discovery systems, and many user facing projects like making it easy to understand error messages on Stripe Checkout. As a Stripe intern, you'll be tackling important projects to increase global commerce, while working alongside exceptional people who insist on doing their best work. You‚Äôll learn from people with high standards who are great at inspiring others to do more and go further. We value technical and personal growth, and see our internship program as a vehicle to foster both.brbrstrongResponsibilitiesbrbrstrongulliWrite software that will be used in production, and has meaningful impact to StripeliliGive and receive technical feedback through code reviews or design discussionsliliCollaborate with other engineers and cross-functional stakeholders to proactively seek and incorporate feedbackliliLearn quickly by asking great questions, by working with your intern manager and teammates effectively, and by communicating the status of your work clearlybrbrbrliulWho you arebrbrWe‚Äôre looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.brbrstrongMinimum RequirementsbrbrstrongulliA strong fundamental understanding of computer science through pursuit of a Bachelor‚Äôs, Master‚Äôs, or PhD degree in computer science, math, or a related disciplineliliSome experience and familiarity with programming, either through side projects or classwork. We work mostly in Java, Ruby, JavaScript, Scala, and Go. We believe new programming languages can be learned if the fundamentals and general knowledge are presentliliExperience from previous internships or other multi-person projects, including open source contributions, that demonstrate evaluating and receiving feedback from mentors, peers, and stakeholdersliliAbility to learn unfamiliar systems and form an understanding of those systems, through independent research and working with a mentor and subject matter expertsbrbrbrliulstrongPreferred QualificationsbrbrstrongulliAt least 2 years of university education, or equivalent work experienceliliOne or more areas of specialized knowledge balanced with general skills and knowledge, such as knowing more frontend technologies and, at a high level, how a service handles an HTTP requestliliUnderstanding and some experience writing high quality pull requests, with good test coverage, and working knowledge to complete projects with minimal defectsliliFamiliarity with navigating and managing your work in new code bases, with multiple languagesliliAbility to write clearly to explain your work to stakeholders, team members, and other StripesbrbrbrliulHybrid work at StripebrbrOffice-assigned Stripes spend at least 50% of the time in a given month in their local office or with users. This hits a balance between bringing people together for in-person collaboration and learning from each other, while supporting flexibility about how to do this in a way that makes sense for individuals and their teams.brbrPay and benefitsbrbrThe annual US base salary range for this role is $123,500 - $123,500. For sales roles, the range provided is the role‚Äôs On Target Earnings ("OTE") range, meaning that the range includes both the sales commissionssales bonuses target and annual base salary for the role. This salary range may be inclusive of several career levels at Stripe and will be narrowed during the interview process based on a number of factors, including the candidate‚Äôs experience, qualifications, and location. Applicants interested in this role and who are not located in the US may request the annual salary range for their location during the interview process.brbrAdditional benefits for this role may include: equity, company bonus or sales commissionsbonuses; 401(k) plan; medical, dental, and vision benefits; and wellness stipends.
